{
  // §23.5: "an operator transition ... creates an ordinary commit with host
  // provenance recorded separately from the application actor field." §22.8:
  // "Only authenticated external interface requests bind $actor. Public requests
  // and engine maintenance run without an actor." A host operator transition
  // runs without an actor, and its provenance is kept SEPARATE from the actor
  // field. But the spec never pins what a model mutation that *reads* `$actor`
  // observes under a host operator transition. Three readings each rest on spec
  // text and SPEC.md chooses none: (a) static rejection at load — §6.2:
  // structural bindings incl. `$actor` "exist only in the feature context that
  // defines them" (authentication), so reading it from an actorless operator
  // mutation could be an invalid package; (b) admission-time rejection — §6.3
  // (line 702): a `$actor` context "MUST receive exactly one occurrence. Zero
  // ... reject that evaluation," and an operator transition binds no actor;
  // (c) a null/absent binding written through to the optional field. This
  // exactly parallels tests/22-runtime-semantics/red/public-request-references-
  // actor-unspecified for the operator path, and additionally leaves unpinned
  // whether the separately-recorded host provenance is application-readable.
  format: 1
  name: operator-commit-actor-provenance-unspecified
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#rust-host", "§23.5", "#runtime", "§22.8", "#expressions", "§6.2", "§6.3"]
  tags: ["operator", "provenance", "actor"]
  note: "Pinned (SPEC-ISSUES #9). §22.8 now states that reading $actor where no actor is bound is an error, never a none binding. A host-operator transition binds no actor, so the mutation reading $actor.id faults at admission as an unbound structural read (§6.3), rejecting the operator call. §22.8 also pins that the host provenance recorded for the transition (§23.5) is not application-readable, so $actor never resolves to it."

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.opprovenance@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      notes: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        body: "text"
        by: "text? = none"
      }
      $mut: {
        // Reads $actor while running with no actor bound (operator path).
        stamp: [
          "n = .notes + { id: @id, body: @body, by: $actor.id }"
          "return n { id, body, by }"
        ]
      }
    }
  }

  steps: [
    { operator: { call: "stamp", args: { id: "n1", body: "hi" } },
      expect: { outcome: rejected, violates: ["#runtime", "§22.8", "#rust-host", "§23.5", "#expressions", "§6.3"] } }
  ]
}
